      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Few people would argue that having a smartphone is something that has dramatically changed how they go about their day. Or how their instant-messaging app of choice has affected how they interact with their family, friends or coworkers.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "So why are people apprehensive at all when confronted with an app that's intended to change their behavior?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Whether it’s apps designed to change how you consume the news, plan your day, stick to your diet, or just relax, solutions abound.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "It’s not a question of ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "will",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " they work for you (they will), it’s a question of what problem are you going to solve, what app are you going to choose, what are you going to commit to today, tomorrow, this week and next, to dramatically improve your life?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Lets not forget that apps—and the product and platforms and people that power them—are a completely new and wondrous invention. Literal and figurative programs (not unlike therapy) thoughtfully researched, crafted, curated, and personalized(?) for you.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Yes. It’s a little crazy to think that something so impactful might be available through the same medium as Angry Birds or Candy Crush, or (even) that a life-changing program ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "could",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " be as cost-effective as $30/month for a premium fee (or just free). It’s a little crazy, but that’s not to say that ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "trying it",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " won’t work. Sure, it might not. But with as little downside (and as much potential upside) do you really not want to?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Maybe it’ll work. Maybe it won’t. Maybe you should try it for yourself and find out.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "…",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
